President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Arkansas due to a severe winter storm that occurred from January 30 to February 2, 2023. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. FEMA's Roland W. Jackson has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.